# Pages and routing (`src/pages/`)

## Layouts

- **Default shell:** Most marketing pages use `BaseLayout` from `src/layouts/BaseLayout.astro` (nav, footer, search, AOS/Tilt). Pass `hideNav` / `hideFooter` when mirroring auth pages like `sign-in.astro` / `sign-up.astro`.
- **Per-type shells:** `BlogLayout`, `WorkLayout`, `TeamLayout`, `ServicesLayout`, `LegalLayout` wrap `BaseLayout` or inner structure — pass `frontmatter={entry.data}` when matching existing dynamic routes.

## Dynamic routes

- **`[...slug].astro`:** `getStaticPaths` uses `getCollection(...)` and `params: { slug: entry.id }` for **`work`**, **`team`**, **`services`**, **`legal`**, and **`posts`** (under `blog/posts/`).
- **Blog tags:** `blog/tags/[tag].astro` — `tag` is a string from `posts` frontmatter `tags`; URLs like `/blog/tags/webdesign`.

## URL reference (this theme)

- Posts: `/blog/posts/<id>`
- Tags: `/blog/tags`, `/blog/tags/<tag>`
- Work: `/work`, `/work/<id>`
- Team: `/team`, `/team/<id>`
- Services: `/services/<id>` (listing lives on homepage `#services`, not a separate index route)
- Legal: `/legal/<id>`
- System kit: `/system/*`
- RSS: `rss.xml.js` → `/rss.xml` (verify feed `glob` matches where posts actually live)

## Edits

- When adding a new **routable** collection, add both **`src/content.config.ts`** and a **`getStaticPaths`** page under `src/pages/`, plus a layout if needed — keep the same `getCollection` + `render(entry)` pattern as `legal/[...slug].astro`.
